reen: </strong>13.3-inch full HD (1,920 x 1,080) &ndash; UHD (3,840 x 2,160) touchscreen | <strong>Storage: </strong>256GB &ndash; 2TB PCIe SSD</p><aside class="hawk-widget-insert _hawk widget_type:price model_names:HP%20Spectre%20x360%20%282019%29 " data-model-name="HP Spectre x360 (2019)" data-widget-type="price"></aside><div class="icon icon-plus_circle _hawk">Very well built</div><div class="icon icon-plus_circle _hawk">Powerful and thin</div><div class="icon icon-minus_circle _hawk">Expensive</div><p>The HP Spectre line of Ultrabooks and 2-in-1 laptops has always consisted of extraordinarily attractive devices. So, when we say that the 2019 Spectre x360 takes things to another level, that should mean something. This is one of the most beautiful laptops on the market right now, with its gem cut design and sleek profile. Couple that with the powerful Intel Whiskey Lake processors and long battery life, and you get one of the best laptops on the market right now. Its ability to flip into a Windows tablet is just icing on the cake.&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Read the full review: </strong><a href="https://www.techradar.com/reviews/hp-spectre-x360-2016">HP Spectre x360 (2019)</a></p><div class="inlinegallery"><div class="inlinegallery-wrap"><div class="inlinegallery-item"><span class="slidecount">Image 1 of 4</span><p class="bordeaux-image-check"><img src="https://vanilla.futurecdn.net/techradar/media/img/missing-image.svg" alt="" class=" lazy-image lazy-image-loading lazyload optional-image" onerror="this.parentNode.replaceChild(window.missingImage(),this)" sizes="auto" data-normal="https://vanilla.futurecdn.net/techradar/media/img/missing-image.svg" data-src="https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/VPsJCRgHtNYH2rx88iqXD9-320-80.jpg" data-srcset="https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/VPsJCRgHtNYH2rx88iqXD9-320-80.jpg 320w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/VPsJCRgHtNYH2rx88iqXD9-650-80.jpg 650w" data-sizes="auto" data-original-mos="https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/VPsJCRgHtNYH2rx8